Table.Name: Question
Table.Description: This table stores the Question independent of Subject

Column.Name: id
Column.Description: System generated Id for Question

Column.Name: question_title
Column.Description: A title or short description of the question being asked

Column.Name: question_formula
Column.Description: The field that will contain the question and latex mark-up language

Column.Name: question_type_id
Column.Description: FK relationship to Question Type

Column.Name: question_category_id
Column.Description: FK relationship to Question category

Column.Name: is_answer_visible
Column.Description: This will govern the visibilty of answer over UI. E.g For fill the blank question, we do not want to show the correct answer during test

Column.Name: date_created
Column.Description: When record got created.

Column.Name: date_modified
Column.Description: When record got modified. Initially when record got inserted,date_created and date_modified will be same. date_modified will get new value once record got modified

Column.Name: is_active
Column.Description: Indicate deleted/active records True=Not Deleted False= Deleted

Column.Name: id
Column.Description: System generated Id for Answer

Column.Name: questions_Id
Column.Description: FK relationship to Question Record

Column.Name: answer_formula
Column.Description: The field that will contain the answer and latex mark-up language

Column.Name: is_correct
Column.Description: Boolean to show which answer is correct for given question

Table.Name: Assessment
Table.Description: This table stores the Assessments

Column.Name: id
Column.Description: System generated Id for record

Column.Name: assessment_name
Column.Description: The name give to the Assessment. Example: Orders of Operations Practice

Column.Name: assessment_description
Column.Description: Any descriptive text used to describe the test or assignment that can be used to display in the UI

Column.Name: version
Column.Description: This will be applicable to only Placement Test. For given topic/Tag there could be multiple version of test.

Column.Name: modified_by
Column.Description: Who modified the record

Column.Name: date_created
Column.Description: When record got created.

Column.Name: date_modified
Column.Description: When record got modified. Initially when record got inserted,date_created and date_modified will be same. date_modified will get new value once record got modified

Column.Name: is_active
Column.Description: Indicate deleted/active records True=Not Deleted False= Deleted

Table.Name: Assessment_Question
Table.Description: This table stores relation between Assessment and Question

Column.Name: id
Column.Description: System generated Id for record

Column.Name: assessment_id
Column.Description: FK relationship to Assessment Record

Column.Name: questions_id
Column.Description: FK relationship to Question ID record

Column.Name: Id
Column.Description: System generated Id for record

Column.Name: test_series_name
Column.Description: User input name for Test Series

Column.Name: Id
Column.Description: System generated Id for record

Column.Name: Assessment_Id
Column.Description: FK relationship to Assessment Record

Column.Name: Test_Series_Id
Column.Description: FK relationship to Test Series Record

Column.Name: id
Column.Description: System generated Id for Placement

Column.Name: test_series_id
Column.Description: FK relationship to Test Series Record

Column.Name: course_name
Column.Description: User input name/title for the course

Column.Name: cooling_period
Column.Description: Picklist values that indicate the amount of time that must pass between a student taking a test and subsequent test

Column.Name: retake_number
Column.Description: The maximum number of placement test re-takes allowed during a course period. We will make tis value a picklist with values ranging from 0-10

Column.Name: pretest_content_review
Column.Description: This value determines if a student will be able to view learning modules before taking the first test. If selected the associated learning modules will be viewable to students before they take the test.
